main event: A UFO sighting in Roswell, New Mexico on June 27, 1965, observed for 20-30 minutes.
interesting points: The object was characterized as possibly being a low flying satellite., The sighting was reported by AIC David R. Mosley and other personnel., Observers noted the object's downward motion from northeast to northwest., There were two groups of observers, and a request was made for motion sequence data from both groups., The object exhibited bright light and no sound was reported during observation.
witness description: AIC David R. Mosley and other personnel
